SIMPLE: intestate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intestate
<hw>In*tes"tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>intestatus</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>testatus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>testari</ets> to make a will: cf. F. <ets>intestat</ets>.
See <er>Testament</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Without having made a valid will; without a will;
<as>as, to die <ex>intestate</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Airy succeeders of <qex>intestate</qex> joys.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not devised or bequeathed; not disposed of by will;
<as>as, an <ex>intestate</ex> estate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intestate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intestate
<hw>In*tes"tate</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A person who
dies without making a valid will.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intestinal</ent>⟦br⟧
